Mitochondrial genes are in the list of most variable genes. Plot the percent MT content to check if it is enriched in adipocytes Ans: No. MT content is not high in cluster enriched for ADIPOQ expression. It is rather placed in the middle right section of the differentiating preadipocytes blob One strategy could be to remove cells with MT content greater than the mean MT content in adipocytes, since these cells are expected to have elevated mitochondrial activity I also want to understand what days are contributing the most to MT content being high. Ans: Day 15 and Day 20. See the section below

s_white[["percent.mt"]] <- PercentageFeatureSet(s_white, pattern = "^MT-")
FeaturePlot(s_white,"percent.mt")

hist(s_white$percent.mt)

For MT content between 10-30%, most of the barcodes are from Day 20, and for MT content between 30% and 70%, most barcodes are from Day 15 and Day 20, and these barcodes do not express ADIPOQ.

mt_content=as.data.frame(s_white$percent.mt)
colnames(mt_content)="percent.mt"
mt_content$barcodes=rownames(mt_content)
mt_content=mt_content[order(mt_content$percent.mt,decreasing = FALSE),]
mt_content$bin=cut(mt_content$percent.mt,breaks=c(-Inf,seq(10, 100, 10)),labels = FALSE)
mt_content$batch.indices=s_white@meta.data[mt_content$barcodes,"batch.indices"]
